commText: Welcome back. CSK have their Impact Player - Dube out, Pathirana in. This will be a very tough chase but don't rule GT out yet. Chahar with a wide slip in.

Rachin Ravindra: It was a pretty good wicket to bat on. The new ball was coming on nicely. It was about showing some intent, good to bat with Ruturaj. The outfields in India are pretty quick, you get pretty good value for your shots. As a player you want to take down the powerplay. It (total) is slightly over par, but still it's a very good wicket. There's slight dew on the oufield. (Will bowl a few overs) hopefully.

21:21 Local Time, 15:51 GMT, 21:21 IST: CSK have amassed a massive total here. Chepauk isn't known to be the truest batting surface in the country and that tells you how well CSK have done today. They were asked to bat first and got off to a flier thanks to Rachin Ravindra. His timing was sublime right from the outset and the runs flowed freely. Ruturaj got an early reprieve as he was dropped at slip in the very first over. Both openers eventually fell for 46 and it looked like GT had pulled things back slightly after the powerplay. Rahane struggled to get going and he was out stumped trying to up the ante. CSK needed to get the momentum back in their favor and Shivam Dube helped them do exactly that. He struck them cleanly right from ball one and he raced along to a 23-ball 51. Mitchell played second-fiddle and a nice little cameo from Rizvi helped take CSK over 200. This might not be a typical Chennai wicket but this total will take some chasing. Back shortly.

Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, out Jadeja Run Out!! 1 run completed. Slower short ball on middle, Jadeja shuffles down the track and heaves it away towards deep mid-wicket, he didn't time it too well, Mitchell was charging back for the second but Jadeja wasn't interested. Jadeja run out (Vijay Shankar/Saha) 7(3) [4s-1]
Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, FOUR, streaky but they'll take it! Yorker fired into off-stump, Mohit Sharma didn't do much wrong there, Jadeja gave away all his stumps and made room, just jammed his bat down on this and got a thick outside edge that raced past the right of short third man

Mohit Sharma to Jadeja, 114.7kph, 2 runs, slower delivery banged in short on middle, Jadeja shuffled well inside the line, got under it and looked to pull it over the man at short fine-leg, went very fine off the edge but was tracked down
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Mohit Sharma to Sameer Rizvi, out Caught by Miller!! Straight down the fielder's throat! Very full and just outside off, undercooked the yorker a touch, Sameer Rizvi stood deep in his crease and he dug it out towards long-on, hit it well but couldn't get under it to get the elevation. Safely held by Miller at long-on, he doesn't make many mistakes. Nonetheless, a valuable cameo from the young man. Sameer Rizvi c Miller b Mohit Sharma 14(6) [6s-2]
Mohit Sharma to Sameer Rizvi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohit Sharma to Sameer Rizvi, 115.7kph, no run, valuable dot ball! Slower short delivery on middle, Sameer Rizvi shuffled across and got inside the line looking to pull it very fine, was just through his shot a shade early and he missed, went over middle-stump
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, 1 run, full and outside off, slapped out towards long-off, straight to the man and only one
The problems compound for GT, they'll be allowed only 4 fielders outside the ring, that's the slow over-rate penalty kicking in

Rashid Khan to Sameer Rizvi, SIX, just over the ropes! A wicket falls but CSK still get 15 off the over. Floated up fuller and just outside off, Sameer Rizvi skipped down the track looking to go down the ground, it looked like he sliced this initially but he got enough to clear long-off
Rashid Khan to Sameer Rizvi, no run, flatter delivery pushed through quick just outside off, wild hack across the line and Sameer Rizvi misses
Rashid Khan to Sameer Rizvi, 2 runs, length delivery just outside off, Sameer Rizvi presses back and slashes it away towards deep point, they get back for two

Rashid Khan to Sameer Rizvi, SIX, Sameer Rizvi gets into the act straightaway! What a way to make an impression! First ball he faces in the IPL and he smokes it for six, full and on the pads, Sameer Rizvi leant in and slog-swept it over deep backward square leg
Sameer Rizvi, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Rashid Khan to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Shankar!! Dube falls! Wrong-un pushed through flat and outside off, Shivam Dube probably didn't pick it off the hand, he hung back and looked to slap it up and over cover, the field was up on the off-side but this one came right off the toe end. It lobbed up and was taken safely by the man running back from extra cover, only had to take a few steps back. Shivam Dube c Shankar b Rashid Khan 51(23) [4s-2 6s-5]
Rashid Khan to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, floated up full on middle-leg, Mitchell cleared his front-leg looking to slog it away and got a thick outside edge that went towards short third man
Rashid Khan [3.0-0-34-1] is back into the attack
Loud cheers for Dhoni every time he's shown on the big screen. Will he give them even more to cheer about by walking out next? Well, the anticipation is definitely there
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, that's 50 for Shivam Dube! Slower delivery into the deck and just outside off again, Shivam Dube pulls it away towards deep square leg and they come back for two

Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, no run, they're not getting a wide for that, review lost! Slower short ball, tennis-ball bounce and it slants across outside off, Shivam Dube pulls out of his shot as it lobs through, expected a wide but it wasn't
CSK review for a wide

Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, 1 run, in the air but lands short! Full and just outside off, Mitchell tried to go over long-off this time but hit it very poorly, that's what saves him as it went flat and landed well short of long-off
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length on middle, mistimed pull goes towards deep mid-wicket

Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 101.6kph, SIX, that's been smoked! Back of the hand slower delivery, strays too full and Shivam Dube spotted it, he waited for it before lofting it effortlessly over long-off
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, 1 run, full and outside off, catches the inner half as Mitchell was looking to loft it over cover, goes along the ground towards long-on
Loud cheer as Dhoni is shown on the big-screen again. Seemed to be watching the game intently.I0$
Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, 123.6kph, 1 run, good length delivery on leg-stump, gently tucked away towards mid-wicket, Mitchell wanted a second but it wasn't there

Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, FOUR, playing the field to perfection! Low full-toss just outside off, overcooked the yorker and Mitchell had spotted fine-leg inside the ring, he shuffled across and just used the pace to scoop it up and over that man
Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, no run, full and just outside off, slants across and beats Mitchell as he swings for the stars

Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, 1 run, excellent stop at mid-off, back of a length delivery outside off, Shivam Dube made a bit of room and slapped it towards mid-off, Gill there was quick to dive to his left to stop it
Dhoni is padded up and is shadow-batting in the dressing room. Meanwhile, Dube's bat is done for after that last delivery, he's got a new one now
Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, 140kph, no run, beautifully bowled, Johnson nails the yorker on off-stump and all Shivam Dube can do is block it
Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, 139.5kph, 1 run, short of length on middle, Mitchell gets no timing on the pull and it only goes as far as mid-wicket

Timeout. Lots of problems for GT right now because they simply cannot seem to find a way to stop the runs. Shivam Dube seems to be in outstanding touch and they've still got a couple of big hitters waiting in the shed. 220 is well on the cards here and the Titans will have to do incredibly well if they are to restrict them to anything under 200.

Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, FOUR, cleverly done! Slower delivery banged into the deck again, only got about waist-high and Shivam Dube waited for it before tucking it fine and to the right of short fine-leg, had enough to beat the fielder running across from deep backward square leg
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, 133kph, 1 run, full and outside off, slapped down to long-off
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, 115.7kph, 2 runs, slower delivery banged in short on middle, Mitchell pulls it away to the right of deep mid-wicket, can't quite find the gap but they get two more
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, 133.4kph, 2 runs, yorker on off-stump, Mitchell clears his front leg and clips it away towards deep mid-wicket, they scurry back for two
Mohit Sharma to Mitchell, 103.7kph, no run, leg-cutter on a length and on leg-stump, Mitchell looked to tuck it fine but couldn't beat short fine-leg
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower short ball on middle, Shivam Dube waits for it and pulls it down to deep backward square leg
Mohit Sharma [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Over summary 11-15 Rahane falls for a low score Spencer ends Gaikwad's innings on 46 Rashid goes for 13 in his 3rd over After 15 overs, CSK are 155/3
Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, 138.4kph, 1 run, to fine leg, full and on the pads, clipped down to fine-leg

Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, 134.5kph, SIX, that's sailed over the ropes! Banged in short on middle, Shivam Dube saw this one alright, got his hands up quickly and crunched the pull to send it well over the long leg ropes

Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, 138kph, FOUR, picked the gap very nicely! Length delivery on middle, just angled into him and Shivam Dube stayed inside the line before using the pace to pull it to the right of fine-leg
Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, 138.1kph, 1 run, back of a length on middle, Mitchell clears his front-leg looking to heave it away
Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short of length just outside off, hurries him and the pull goes towards mid-on off the splice
Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, 137kph, 1 run, back of a length on middle, Mitchell looks to pull but is slightly cramped for room, hits his midriff and dribbles into the off-side and they pinch a run

Rashid Khan to Shivam Dube, SIX, Shivam Dube is hitting them as clean as a whistle tonight! Tossed up full on off-stump, Shivam Dube leans into it and slogs it up and over long-on, went high and landed comfortably into the stands
Rashid Khan going round the wicket for the last delivery
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, length delivery on middle, worked away towards deep mid-wicket

Rashid Khan to Mitchell, FOUR, this time he gets it through! Flatter length delivery on off-stump, Mitchell leant in and reverse-swept it squarer this time to get it to the right of short third, man at deep point dived across but couldn't stop it cleanly
Rashid Khan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, flatter delivery on middle-leg, worked away towards deep square leg, Mitchell was looking for a second but it wasn't there
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, full just outside off, Mitchell leans in and pushes it towards long-on
Rashid Khan to Mitchell, no run, full just outside off, Mitchell leans in and plays a reverse-sweep, can't beat short third man though
Rashid Khan [2.0-0-21-1] is back into the attack
Slip in place as Rashid is back
Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, no run, good length delivery just outside off, Shivam Dube hangs back and dabs it straight to short third man
Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, 140.5kph, 1 run, pitched up full on middle, Mitchell clears his front leg a touch and knocks it towards mid-on for a quick single
Spencer Johnson to Mitchell, no run, full and just outside off, knocked towards cover
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, out Caught by Saha!! Loud appeal for caught behind and given! It needed a bit of an appeal from the Titans for the umpire to raise the finger and Gaikwad walked, he knew he'd got something on this. Just short of length and slanting across outside off, Gaikwad hung back looking to heave it away, perhaps didn't quite have enough room and he got a faint inside edge that went through to the keeper. Timely wicket for the Titans. Gaikwad c Saha b Spencer Johnson 46(36) [4s-5 6s-1]
Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, no run, 141.2kph, full and slanting across outside off, Gaikwad mistimes a drive that goes straight to extra cover
Spencer Johnson to Shivam Dube, 138kph, 1 run, back of a length just outside off, Shivam Dube swats it down towards long-on as it gets to about rib-height
Spencer Johnson [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 134.9kph, 1 run, pitched up full on off-stump, driven straight to mid-off, they pinch a quick single

Mohit Sharma to Gaikwad, 133kph, 1 run, length delivery on middle-leg, followed the batter as he looked to make some room, Gaikwad bunted it back hard into the pitch and it lobbed over the bowler before going towards long-off
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 129.7kph, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, rises to about chest-high, Shivam Dube stands tall and heaves it away towards wide long-on, didn't hit it cleanly
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, wide, banged in short, it was just down leg and it's been called a wide, also called one for the over
Mohit Sharma to Gaikwad, 130.5kph, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, tamely bunted towards mid-wicket for one
Mohit Sharma to Shivam Dube, 133.7kph, 1 run, good length delivery slanting across outside off, eased down to third man
Mohit Sharma to Gaikwad, 130.3kph, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, tucked away towards deep mid-wicket
Mohit Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, 1 run, leading edge but safe! Tossed up full outside off, Gaikwad skipped down the track and closed the face of the bat looking to work it into the leg-side, it took the leading edge and floated safely over extra cover. Still, big over that - 15 off it
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, no run, full on off-stump, Gaikwad presses forward and knocks it to the left of the bowler
Sai Kishore to Shivam Dube, 1 run, full on off-stump, pushed down the ground to long on
Sai Kishore to Shivam Dube, wide, flatter delivery and fired wide outside off, goes with the angle and Shivam Dube lets it go
Change of angle previous delivery as well, Sai Kishore is bowling round the wicket

Sai Kishore to Shivam Dube, SIX, two in a row! Shivam Dube getting into his work and how! This wasn't such a bad delivery, flatter and just fuller than a good length, Shivam Dube leant in again and his reach enabled him to slog it away cleanly over deep mid-wicket this time

Sai Kishore to Shivam Dube, SIX, Shivam Dube wastes no time! Floated up full on off-stump, right in the slot and Shivam Dube leans in and smokes this clean over long-on, it goes 87m back! What a hit first ball!
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Sai Kishore to Rahane, out Stumped!! It wasn't happening for Rahane today and he perishes! Rahane was kept quiet and something had to give here. A flatter length delivery on middle, fired in and Rahane had made up his mind to run at this. He came down the track and hacked at it wildly across the line before missing, easiest of stumpings for Saha. He collected it over middle-stump and Rahane was halfway down the pitch. Rahane st Saha b Sai Kishore 12(12)
Sai Kishore to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Stumped!!
Over summary 6-10 Rashid gets the dangerous Rachin R Sai Kishore stats with a frugal over Rashid goes for 10 in his 2nd over Spencer concedes a six off his first ball After 10 overs, CSK are 104/1
STAT: Spencer Johnson has started his spell conceding a six off the first ball in both the games so far (Brevis vs MI, Ruturaj vs CSK)
Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, FOUR, an expensive start by Spencer Johnson. On a length around off and Gaikwad lofts it over the bowler's head to end the over with four runs, 12 from it
Spencer Johnson to Rahane, 1 run, 100 up for CSK! Short and quick on leg, Rahane goes for a pull, gets hurried due to the pace, mistimes it to fine leg for one
Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, 1 run, pitched up by the bowler on off, Gaikwad drives it to mid-off and scampers across to the other end
Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, no run, on the shorter side as Gaikwad pulls it towards mid-on along the turf
Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, no run, 138kph, back of a length outside off, skids along the deck as Gaikwad gets beaten on the cut

Spencer Johnson to Gaikwad, SIX, welcome into the attack Mr. Spencer Johnson! A short and quick delivery, Gaikwad gets into position quickly and nails the pull over deep mid-wicket for half-a-dozen, just clears the boundary
Spencer Johnson, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Strategic timeout! CSK off to fine start. The run rate has dipped a little since Ravindra's dismissal, but with plenty of power-hitters to come, CSK can fancy their chances to post a 190-run total, or even more..
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, 1 run, drifting on the pads, Gaikwad nudges it through square leg for a single
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, 2 runs, short and wide outside off, Gaikwad cuts it through point for a couple of runs
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, no run, width on offer, Gaikwad cuts it to the fielder at backward point
Sai Kishore to Rahane, 1 run, quicker through the air, Rahane nudges it towards mid-on for a single

Sai Kishore to Rahane, 4 runs, misfield and excellent running between the wickets as well. Rahane had nudged this towards deep mid-wicket and the ball beats a couple of fielders in the deep. They run four!
Sai Kishore to Rahane, no run, slower through the air, Rahane slices it to the fielder at point
Ruturaj vs Rashid (before today) 60 balls 95 runs Avg 47.50 SR 158.33
Rashid Khan to Rahane, 1 run, 10 runs from the over as Rahane rocks back in the crease and slices it through point for one
Rashid Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, that was short and Gaikwad was back in the crease to pull it to deep mid-wicket for a single
Rashid Khan to Rahane, 1 run, tad short on middle and leg, nudged towards the on-side by Rahane for a single
Rashid Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, drives this to mid-off where the fielder gets his hands to it, parrying it to the deep
Rashid Khan to Gaikwad, FOUR, pitched up by the bowler outside off, Gaikwad lunges forward and drives it uppishly over cover for four runs. Runs coming thick and fast despite the wicket
Rashid Khan to Gaikwad, 2 runs, short and wide outside off, Gaikwad cuts it through backward point for a couple of runs
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, 1 run, tad short on middle and leg, nudged to wide long-on for a single
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, no run, loopy delivery on off, Gaikwad drives it to cover
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, wide, fired down the leg-side and it's a wide ball
Sai Kishore to Rahane, 1 run, fired down the leg-side, swept to fine leg for a single
Sai Kishore to Rahane, no run, pushed to cover as the bowler goes full
Sai Kishore to Gaikwad, 1 run, makes room and drives the floated delivery to long-off for one
Sai Kishore to Rahane, 1 run, on a length around middle and leg, clipped to the leg-side for a single
Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Rashid Khan to Gaikwad, FOUR, CSK - 69/1 after 6 overs. This was on the shorter side and Gaikwad rocks back in the crease to punch it through the off-side for a boundary to end the powerplay. CSK off to a fantastic start
Rashid Khan to Rahane, 1 run, tad fuller on middle and leg, Rahane clips it through the on-side for one
Rashid Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, nudges the flatter delivery to long-on for one
Rashid Khan to Rahane, 1 run, tad short on off, Rahane punches it to cover for a single to open his account
Ajinkya Rahane, right handed bat, comes to the crease
STAT: Third successive 50+ opening partnership for CSK vs GT

Rashid Khan to Ravindra, out Stumped!! Rashid Khan strikes in his first over, gets the dangerman. Was a quicker delivery on leg and it skids along the deck. Ravindra tries to nudge it away, but gets an inside-edge which rolls towards the keeper. Ravindra was outside his crease and Saha was quick enough to gather the ball and dislodge the bails. The batter was comfortably out of his crease and he misses out on a well-deserved half-century by four runs. Ravindra st Saha b Rashid Khan 46(20) [4s-6 6s-3]
Rashid Khan to Ravindra, THATS OUT!! Stumped!!
Rashid Khan to Ravindra, FOUR, even Rashid Khan is greeted with a boundary. A short ball on off, Ravindra rocks back in the crease and punches it through cover for four runs
Rashid Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Over summary 1-5 R Sai Kishore drops Gaikwad on 1 Rachin gets going with a six and a four Rachin keeps his aggressive intent going 16 comes off the fourth over After 5 overs, CSK are 58/0
Azmatullah to Ravindra, 1 run, short of a length around off, Ravindra slaps it to mid-off for a single to end the over. 45 runs from the last three overs
Azmatullah to Ravindra, wide, way too wide outside off, on the shorter side as Ravindra shoulders arms
Sounds of 'Rachin, Rachin,' engulf the Chepauk
Azmatullah to Ravindra, FOUR, short and wide outside off, Ravindra throws his hands at it, smashing it through cover for four more. Moves into the 40s as a result of this boundary
Azmatullah to Ravindra, no run, short and quick on middle and leg, Ravindra goes for a pull, gets beaten on the top edge, good take by Saha

Azmatullah to Ravindra, SIX, 50 up for CSK! Short of a length around off, Ravindra stands tall and smokes it over wide long-on for half-a-dozen. That was clean as a whistle. Gaikwad walks up to his partner and appreciates him

Azmatullah to Gaikwad, leg byes, 1 run, appeal for an lbw turned down! The impact was way too high. Back of a length delivery on leg as it clips the batter on the thigh pad and rolls into the off-side, a leg bye taken
Azmatullah to Gaikwad, FOUR, impressive. This was pitched up by the bowler and Gaikwad creams it through cover with impeccable timing. Gill puts in a dive in the deep, but to no avail
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, no run, on the shorter side, Ravindra sways away. 16 runs from this over, even better for CSK
Umesh Yadav to Gaikwad, 1 run, back of a length around off, Gaikwad steers it to point for a quick run

Umesh Yadav to Gaikwad, FOUR, if Ravindra is all about power, here is a touch of finesse. Short of a length outside off, Gaikwad plays it late, steering it towards square third man where Mohit Sharma fails to stop the ball despite a dive. Umesh under pressure
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, 1 run, yorker length ball on off, Ravindra digs it towards mid-off for a quick run

Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, FOUR, smashed away! Width on offer and Ravindra has smashed it through cover uppishly, right into the gap and that's four more. No respite for the cheerleaders, they have been in action right throughout
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, SIX, Ravindra dealing in boundaries. This is what he is known for. Back of a length around off, Ravindra stands tall and thumps it over long-on for a 79 metre maximum
Azmatullah to Ravindra, 1 run, 12 runs from the over. On a length around off, Ravindra slices it through backward point for a single to end the over
Azmatullah to Ravindra, FOUR, glorious! Azmatullah goes full and Ravindra drills it straight past the pacer for a boundary more. The fielder at mid-on had no chance to converge and stop it
Azmatullah to Ravindra, FOUR, shot! Short of a length around off, Ravindra pulls it mid-wicket for four more. He's off to a brisk start

Azmatullah to Gaikwad, 1 run, 137.9kph, on a length around leg, Gaikwad flicks it uppishly to deep square leg, but the timing wasn't good enough for it to go the distance, drops well in front of the fielder charging in from the boundary
Azmatullah to Gaikwad, no run, dances down the wicket and drives the length ball crisply to cover does Gaikwad
Azmatullah to Gaikwad, 2 runs, back of a length on middle and leg, Gaikwad advances down the track and clips it through square leg for a couple of runs

Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, no run, edged but safe again! Both the batters living dangerously. Short of a length outside off and Ravindra has a poke at it. Gets a thick outside edge that flies towards slip, but this falls in front of Sai Kishore. Didn't carry probably
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, FOUR, width on offer and Ravindra cashes in. Throws the kitchen sink at it and slices it over point for a rollicking boundary. A couple of loose deliveries by Umesh Yadav
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, SIX, first maximum of the match! Short of a length on leg, Ravindra stays put and flicks it over deep backward fine leg for a flat six. Nonchalantly done!
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, wide, wayward delivery down the leg-side, it's a wide ball as Ravindra goes for a pull and misses
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, no run, pitched up by the bowler on off, Ravindra drives it on the rise to mid-off, was in the air for a while, but didn't carry to the fielder
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, no run, short of a length around off, Ravindra stands tall and punches it to cover
Umesh Yadav to Ravindra, no run, short and wide outside off, Ravindra cuts it towards cover-point
Umesh Yadav, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Azmatullah to Gaikwad, no run, dropped! Regulation catch put down. Short of a length outside off, shaping away from the batter, Gaikwad plays away from his body and gets an outside edge. Flies straight to first slip where Sai Kishore spills it. How costly a dropped catch will it prove to be?
Azmatullah to Gaikwad, no run, on a length around off, Gaikwad opens the bat face, steering this to the fielder at point
Azmatullah to Gaikwad, no run, nice line and length, shaping away from the batter outside off, Gaikwad shoulders arms
Azmatullah to Ravindra, 1 run, drifting on the pads, slightly short as Ravindra glances it to fine leg for a single
Azmatullah to Gaikwad, 1 run, 131.4kph, short of a length around middle and leg, nudged towards wide mid-on by Gaikwad for a single
Azmatullah to Gaikwad, no run, short of a length around off, shaping away from the batter as Gaikwad steers it to point
Gaikwad and Ravindra are at the crease. Gaikwad is on strike. Azmatullah will open the attack
